<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Evening news bits from Gordon Wrinn</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=232849" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/019686.html">Why are Ragebringers so "Easy"?</a></B><P>

Why are Ragebringers so "Easy"? <P>

<B>Essentially, the designer was a little optimistic. It became a little more difficult in the last patch and will probably undergo several more adjustments in the near future.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/019789.html">Trade robbing...banable?</a></B><P>

I was in Freeport today and I met a friend in which I was going to trade with. I walked up to her and about 2 seconds later wham this naked newbie jumped right between us and just stood there. So my question is: If this situation occurs again, and an 'accidental' trade is made to the wrong person, will a GM do anything?<P>

<B>My best advice is to be careful. Be sure that the person you are trading with is the one who is actually intended to receive the items. Sure, we don't want to see the activity mentioned in the beginning occuring, at the same time we don't want to see equally despicable players setting unsuspecting people up and using the GMs as an offensive tool.<P>

The best offense is a strong defense. You are ultimately responsible for who you hand your items to.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/019815.html">People getting away with cheating/duping of plat on Prexus?</a></B><P>

How the heck is it possable to aquire 40,000 platinum? let alone be auctioning multiples of 40,000 to anyone who wants to get it? I been playing this game since about a week after the release and have NEVER even gotten close to 40,000 platinum let alone have the resources available to sell 40,000 platinum to anyone that wants to buy it..<P>

<B>I sincerely doubt that there are any game-damaging dupes out there. We've had the reward offer out there for some time, and only received one that was verifiable, and that was a dupe of soulbound items which are all nodrop anyway. <P>

Here's a copy of the reward offer:<P>

Hello all,<P>

For those who are new to online games, a “dupe” is a bug that allows
a player to “duplicate” or “copy” items, creating two items where once
there was one. We've heard some reports that there may be a dupe bug
somewhere in game. While we're confident that we do not have any current
issues of this type, we'd like to provide an incentive to everyone to
report such things should they become aware of them.<P>

The FIRST person to submit reproduction steps for any dupe bug will
receive the following: a) A free EverQuest account. We'll mark your
current account as free, or provide you with a new, free account,
and b) Subject to approval by us, the title of your choice will be
applied to one of the characters on your account.<P>

To qualify, you must include all of the information below. Furthermore,
THE REPRODUCTION INSTRUCTIONS MUST BE CLEAR, CONCISE, AND PRESENT
LOGICAL STEPS ALLOWING OUR TEST DEPARTMENT TO REPRODUCE THE BUG.
Send an email with a subject line of "Dupe Bug Report" to
<a href="mailto:eqmail@verant.com">eqmail@verant.com</a> containing the following:<P>

1. Station Name<BR>
2. Real Name<BR>
3. Phone Number (Day and Evening)<BR>
4. Primary Play Server<BR>
5. Primary Character Name<BR>
6. Complete reproduction instructions. <P>

“Dupe Bug Reports” will only be considered if they contain all necessary
elements of information including complete instructions for reproducing
the bug. While we appreciate notification of all potential problems,
only concrete first-hand experiences will be considered for the award.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/019896.html">Why do you do this?</a></B><P>

I just found out from a reliable source that EQ checks the CHAT/LOGIN server every time you zone? Could this be why I always get dropped when I zone?<P>

<B>The client doesn't check back with the login server when zoning. As many are aware, we've taken the login server down several times while leaving all of the game servers up. If this was the case, people would get kicked out in masses any time we did this.<P>

I'm not sure why you get dropped when you zone. You might consider deleting all of your OPT files in your EverQuest directory (you'll have to reset customizations). You should also run a "Thorough File Check" from the patch program. <P>

What speed is your connection?<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/019913.html">A very simple question Abashi - No Flaming</a></B><P>

What are your thoughts Abashi?<P>

<B>There are certainly people who feel the same as you do in regards to roleplay. My best suggestion would be to seek them out and group with them. You're not the only one :)<P>

You could also consider starting over on one of the Team servers, where people tend to follow your ideals. I've always found the team servers very conducive to roleplay, even when grouping with people who haven't done it before.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/019989.html">Request for /loc code in text (such as %L)</a></B><P>

They won't do it. They don't like /loc in the game as it is, so they won't do anything else that would justify its use.<P>

<B>That's pretty accurate. We certainly don't want to broaden it's usefulness.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/020059.html">Abashi, can I get a guarantee that my Epic Quest reward will not be nerfed?</a></B><P>

On behalf of them, I am asking for a 'Guarantee' that these weapons have been playtested, and that the Epic Quest rewards will not be altered in any way that would lower its effectiveness in any way.<P>

<B>I can't give you the guarantee that nothing will change. In fact, the fact that the rogue weapon is equipable in the ranged slot was a mistake that will be corrected in the next patch.<P> 

Though I don't expect any more changes, we need to leave that possibility open.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/020060.html">Most hated Norrath villain??</a></B><P>

HOLLY WINDSTALKER<BR>
CROS TREEWIND<P>

<B>They have my vote :)<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
